President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Robert Wilkie of North Carolina as the Secretary of Veterans Affairs. Wilkie has been serving as the Acting Secretary of Veterans Affairs since March 2018 and as the Under Secretary of Defense for Personnel and Readiness since November 2017. He has previously worked as a senior advisor to Senator Thom Tillis, as well as in the Presidential transition office and in various positions within the George W. Bush Administration. Wilkie is currently serving in the United States Air Force Reserve and has a strong educational background, including degrees from Wake Forest University, Loyola University College of Law, Georgetown University Law Center, and the United States Army War College.